1. First we create a working sheet so that we can save the raw data.

2. Remove Duplicates first.
->Data-> Data Cleanup -> Remove duplicates.

3.Replcae the abbreviation with full name. For instance M -> Male, F ->Female.
Goto edit-> Find and replace.

4.Remove the Currency symbol.
Goto Format-> Number(If needed)
Remove decial points.

5.To make a range of age group we use the If statments:
=IF(L2>54,"Old", IF(L2>=31,"Middle Age",IF(L2<31,"Adolescent","Invalid")))

6. Creating a Pivot Table.
First create a Pivot Table =>Insert-> Pivot Table
Select the worksheet after selecting all the values of it.

7.Creating a multiple Pivot table on the same sheet.
We select the Pivot table creation and then we select the existing sheet and then select cell where we want to create pivot table.

8.Create a Pivot chart and make dashboard. Also we can use pivot slicer for creating filteration.
-> Pivot Analyzer ->Insert slicer 
Insert slicer helps provide filteration on the basis of a particular values.
